  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6956 sitting just above the max positive gamma wall at 6950 (19.6B), dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX concentration between 6950-7000 suggests dealers will continue to fade moves in either direction, keeping price magnetically pulled toward these high gamma strikes. Key levels to watch: 6950 as immediate resistance where selling pressure intensifies, 6848 GEX flip as the regime boundary, and 6800 where dealer buying would accelerate on any breakdown.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6950-7000 with dealers capping upside momentum.",
